<font color="#FF0000">ADIOS</font><br>
<tt>Sun Feb 22 16:33:35 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
Time to say adios to this site.<br><br>
Needless to say it has been fun and more important enlightening and rewarding.<br><br>
I always appreciated the opinions of others.  I know what I think.  Vietnam remains a complicated issue and will so for the rest of my life.  To me the war paralleled human nature -- at its best and worst.<br><br>
I have been thinking for the last two days what I wanted to write for my last words on this site.<br><br>
Participation in the war stripped away the illusions of my youth and life in general.  Creating singular moments of joy in the lives of others became a general focus for many years.<br><br>
Thoreau once wrote that we, people, live lives of quiet desperation.  I read that years ago and still believe it to a large extent.<br><br>
I truly believe that when our stories are absorbed on deeper levels that the world will learn a few lessons and that our children and grandchildren will reap the benefits.<br><br>
Thanks to Marc for his efforts and to the rest of you for willing to put your souls on the line for all to read.<br><br>
Paul Mahar<br>

